{{Infobox examination | name = Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board | image_name = Official JAMB logo.png | image_size = 220px | image_alt = | caption = Official logo | acronym = JAMB | type = Computer-Based Test | skills_tested = Academic performance in selected subjects. | purpose = Admission into tertiary institution. | year_started = {{Start date|1978}} | year_terminated = | duration = 2 hours. | score_range = 0 to 400 | score_validity = 1 year | offered = Once in a year | regions = [[Nigeria]] | language = [[English language|English]] | test_takers = More than one million | prerequisite = SSCE results or awaiting SSCE results. | score_users = Over 500 universities, agencies and other institutions in Nigeria. | qualification_rate = | free_label = | free = | website = {{URL|www.jamb.org.ng}} | footnotes = }}
The '''Joint Admissions and Matriculations Board''' ('''JAMB''') is a [[Nigerian]] entrance examination board for tertiary-level institutions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2012/04/ojerinde-re-appointed-jamb-registrar/|title=Ojerinde re-appointed JAMB registrar|date=9 April 2012|work=Vanguard News}}</ref> The board conducts entrance [[Test (assessment)|examinations]] for prospective undergraduates into [[Nigeria]]n universities. The board is also charged with the responsibility to administer similar examinations for applicants to Nigerian public and private monotechnics, [[Institute of technology|polytechnics]], and colleges of educations. All of these candidates must have obtained the West Africa School Certificate, now [[West African Examinations Council]], WAEC, or its equivalent, [[National Examination Council (Nigeria)]], NECO.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/varsities-set-irrelevant-post-utme-questions-and-blame-candidates-for-failing-prof-dibu-ojerinde-jamb-boss/|title=Varsities set irrelevant post-UTME questions and blame candidates for failing – Prof. Dibu Ojerinde, JAMB boss|work=The Punch - Nigeria's Most Widely Read Newspaper|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213140913/http://www.punchng.com/news/varsities-set-irrelevant-post-utme-questions-and-blame-candidates-for-failing-prof-dibu-ojerinde-jamb-boss/|archivedate=2014-12-13|df=}}</ref>
The pioneer Registrar was Mr. Michael Saidu Angulu who served from inception in 1978 to 1986.
