{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Klaus Wunder | fullname = Klaus Wunder | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1950|09|13|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Erfurt]], [[East Germany]] | position = [[Forward (association football)|Striker]] | height = {{Height|m=1.76}} | years1 = 1969–1971 | caps1 = | goals1 = | clubs1 = [[SV Arminia Hannover|Arminia Hannover]] | years2 = 1970–1974 | caps2 = 94 | goals2 = 32 | clubs2 = [[MSV Duisburg]] | years3 = 1974–1976 | caps3 = 43 | goals3 = 7 | clubs3 = [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] | years4 = 1976–1978 | caps4 = 75 | goals4 = 33 | clubs4 = [[Hannover 96]] | years5 = 1978–1980 | caps5 = 56 | goals5 = 12 | clubs5 = [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] | nationalyears1= 1970–1972 | nationalcaps1= 20 | nationalgoals1= 6 | nationalteam1= [[Germany Olympic football team|West Germany Amateur]] | nationalyears2= 1972–1973 | nationalcaps2= 5 | nationalgoals2= 4 | nationalteam2= [[Germany national under-21 football team|West Germany U-23]] | nationalyears3= 1972–1974 | nationalcaps3= 3 | nationalgoals3= 0 | nationalteam3= [[Germany national football B team|West Germany B]] | nationalyears4= 1973 | nationalcaps4= 1 | nationalgoals4= 0 | nationalteam4= [[Germany national football team|West Germany]] }}
'''Klaus Wunder''' (born 13 September 1950 in [[Erfurt]]) is a former [[Germany|German]] [[Association football|footballer]] who played for [[FC Bayern Munich]] and was part of their [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]] victory in [[1974–75 European Cup|1975]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/1-bundesliga/1979-80/werder-bremen-4/13439/spieler_klaus-wunder.html|title=Wunder, Klaus|work=[[kicker (sports magazine)|kicker.de]]|accessdate=16 April 2013|language=German}}</ref> He earned one cap for the [[Germany national football team]] and also represented [[West Germany at the 1972 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Sports Reference|title=Profile at sports-reference.com|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/wu/klaus-wunder-1.html|accessdate=16 April 2013}}</ref>
== Honours == * [[1975 European Cup Final|1975 European Cup]] winner
